ttps://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/billie-eilish-robert-smith@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/billie-eilish-robert-smith@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/billie-eilish-robert-smith@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/billie-eilish-robert-smith@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robert-smith">Robert Smith</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stevie-wonder">Stevie Wonder</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nicki-minaj">Nicki Minaj</a>等少数艺术家签署了一封公开信，警告人们不要在音乐中“掠夺性”使用<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/ai">人工智能 (AI)</a> 。 </p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="39" data-list-defn-props="{&quot;335552541&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559684&quot;:-2,&quot;335559685&quot;:720,&quot;335559991&quot;:360,&quot;469769226&quot;:&quot;Symbol&quot;,&quot;469769242&quot;:[8226],&quot;469777803&quot;:&quot;left&quot;,&quot;469777804&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;469777815&quot;:&quot;hybridMultilevel&quot;}" aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-posinset="1" data-aria-level="1"><b>阅读更多：</b><b> </b><a href="https://www.nme.com/features/how-ai-is-pushing-the-boundaries-of-entertainment-3409263"><b>超越人类想象：人工智能如何突破娱乐界限</b></a></li></ul><p>昨天（4 月 2 日），非盈利组织艺术家权利联盟发表了一封题为“停止贬低音乐”的公开信，内容涉及人工智能在音乐领域的崛起，由超过 200 名音乐界知名人士签名。 <a href="https://artistrightsnow.medium.com/200-artists-urge-tech-platforms-stop-devaluing-music-559fb109bbac">请在此处阅读全文</a>。</p><p>通过这封信，这家由艺术家运营的非营利组织要求开发商、技术公司、平台和数字音乐服务“承诺不会开发或部署破坏或取代人类艺术的人工智能音乐生成技术、内容或工具”。词曲作者和艺术家，或者拒绝为我们的工作提供公平的报酬。”</p><p>信中指出：“毫无疑问：我们相信，如果负责任地使用，人工智能具有巨大的潜力，可以提高人类的创造力，并为世界各地的音乐迷提供新的、令人兴奋的体验的开发和增长。” </p><figure id="attachment_3506553" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3506553" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3506553" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images.jpg" alt="比莉·艾利什" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/billie-eilish-getty-Nykieria-Chaney_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3506553" class="wp-caption-text">比莉·艾利什.图片来源：Nykieria Chaney/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> “不幸的是，一些平台和开发商正在利用人工智能来破坏创造力并损害艺术家、歌曲作者、音乐家和版权所有者的利益。如果不负责任地使用人工智能，就会对我们保护隐私、身份、音乐和生计的能力构成巨大威胁。”</p><p>公开信继续说道：“一些最大、最有实力的公司在未经许可的情况下，利用我们的工作来训练人工智能模型。这些努力的直接目的是用大量人工智能创建的“声音”和“图像”取代人类艺术家的作品，从而大大稀释支付给艺术家的版税池。对于许多只是想维持收支平衡的职业音乐家、艺术家和词曲作者来说，这将是灾难性的。”</p><p> “如果不加以控制，人工智能将引发一场逐底竞争，这将降低我们工作的价值，并使我们无法获得公平的补偿。必须停止这种对人类创造力的攻击。我们必须防止人工智能被掠夺性地使用来窃取专业艺术家的声音和肖像、侵犯创作者的权利并破坏音乐生态系统。” </p><figure id="attachment_3581903" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3581903" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3581903" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024.jpg" alt="史蒂夫旺德" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/stevie_wonder_2024-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3581903" class="wp-caption-text">史蒂夫·旺德. （丹尼尔·奈顿/盖蒂图片社拍摄）</figcaption></figure><p>除了上述艺术家之外，其他签署该文件的音乐家还包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/katy-perry">Katy Perry</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sam-smith">Sam Smith</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kim-petras">Kim Petras</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/r-e-m">REM</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jon-bon-jovi">Jon Bon Jovi</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mumford-sons">Mumford &amp; Sons</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/imagine-dragons">Imagine Dragons</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/d4vd">d4vd</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jon-batiste">Jon Batiste</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/finneas">Finneas</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/fletcher">Fletcher</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/pearl-jam">Pearl Jam</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/j-balvin">J Balvin</a> 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jonas-brothers">乔纳斯兄弟</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noah-kahan">诺亚·卡汉</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/norah-jones">诺拉·琼斯</a>、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/yard-act">Yard Act</a> 、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-last-dinner-party">最后的晚宴</a>、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/zayn-malik">Zayn Malik</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/smokey-robinson">Smokey Robinson</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sheryl-crow">Sheryl Crow</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sigrid">Sigrid</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/bob-marley">Bob Marley</a>和<a href="http